<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,260,285]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[344,638,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavernosium">
<emphasis box="[344,638,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Allometopon cavernosium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a relatively pale 
<collectingCountry box="[857,1074,260,285]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
species characterized by a short to long medial stripe, a yellow scutellum that is brown on the dorsal surface, no brown markings on the first flagellomere or the back of the head, and a yellow epandrium with a brown dorsobasal spot. The male terminalia are particularly diagnostic, with the surstylus subrectangular with a large posteromedial process, and the phallapodeme especially large and cavernous with no vestige of the apical section of the rod remaining.
</paragraph>
